				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have a question for everyone to think about for the Hell lvls. Now I already know what the people who are for the hell lvl removal will say so this is more directed towards those who do not favor it. Just imagine if VI added and option upon character creation that allowed you to play the game with hell lvls or without. Now since 2 characters starting at the same and gaining the same exact exp at the same time (one with hell lvls and one without) they will reach 60 at the EXACT same time, I know its been stated before but I'm stressing. Now for those of you not in favor of removing the hell lvls would you actually play the game with them or without them? Stay open minded about this. I am really curious about the no retro exp thing though. If they dont allow for it  and when they spread the exp out per lvl that means that you will lose exp points and it will take even longer to reach lvl 60.<BR>
<BR>
If i'm understanding this retro exp thing correctly it will mean that when the change goes into effect the exp per lvl will be spread and you will keep the same exact lvl and exp bar position you had previously. Now if your lvl 46 and gone through those hell lvls that would mean you would prolly jump up to lvl 47 or 48 because youve gained so much exp and when they released that tension of hell lvls you current amount of exp (not lvl but number of points) has to go some where and with its coiling up like a spring back in the hell lvls its would only pop forward.. but not much. pre hell would be effected as much. So you see they must take away exp points somewhere in order for you to keep the same lvl without having a backlash of exp.<BR>
<BR>
I for one like the removal of the hell lvls, it will make the game alot smoother... NOT EASIER. but this no retro exp kinda bothers me since we will lose exp points that we have worked for so hard through the hell. I may have my math all wrong but it appears to be logical. Correct me if I messed up some where.<BR>
<BR>
&quot;Closed minded people annoy me, but ignorance is bliss&quot;
